column12: CLUTCH AND BICYCLE FOR A CHILD INCLUDING THE SAME
column13: PURPOSE: A bicycle clutch and a bicycle for an infant thereof are provided to control selectively the connection a pedal with a wheel, wherein an infant determines the timing when operating bicycle pedals forward. CONSTITUTION: A bicycle clutch(100) includes an outer ring(10), an inner ring(20), and a latch bolt(30). The outer ring has an inner circumference on which the latch is formed. The inner ring has an outer circumference including at least one convex type recess part. The inner ring includes a latch bolt seating surface extended to the outer circumference of the inner ring from the convex type recess part. The convex type recess part has a part of the convex type recess recessed into the space in the inner circumference of the outer ring. The latch bolt has one end(30a) having the curved surface corresponding to the convex type recess part of the inner ring and the other end(30b) capable of hanging on the latch. The latch bolt rotates in a constant angular range for the other end of the latch bolt to be hanged loosed on the latch. [Reference numerals] (AA) Back; (BB) Front

column12: RPM FLOATING PREVENTION METHOD FOR IDLING STATE
column13: PURPOSE: A method for preventing floating of rpm is provided to improve convenience and safety for a driver by operating TPS(Throttle Position Sensor) learning control when a specific condition is satisfied and operating general TPS control in other situations. CONSTITUTION: An rpm floating preventing method comprises the steps of: operating TPS learning control when a vehicle is stopped and is in a normal state and operating general TPS control in other situations; operating general TPS control if retardant time period is over a specific value when TPS output is lower than TPS learning value by a difference over a specific value; and controlling a TPS learning value with a TPS filtering value if the retardant time period is over the specific value or operating general TPS control in other situations. Therefore, CTS(Closed Throttle Sensor) is kept in an on state in an idle state and floating of engine rpm is avoided.
column15: CHUNG BYONG-YONG

column13: 본 고안은 센스앰프 구동회로에 관한 것으로, 종래에는 전원전압전달라인 및 접지전위전달라인의 저항에 의해 센스앰프구동부로부터 거리가 멀어질수록 전압강하 및 전류집중현상에 의해 센스앰프의 구동시간이 늦어짐으로써, 고집적화가 어려운 문제점과; 센스앰프구동부에 피모스트랜지스터 및 엔모스트랜지스터가 동시에 존재함으로써, 기판면적이 증가하는 문제점이 있었다. 이와같은 문제점을 감안한 본 고안은 제1외부제어신호에 의해 전원전압을 인가 또는 차단하는 다수의 피모스트랜지스터 및 제2외부제어신호에 의해 접지전위를 인가 또는 차단하는 다수의 엔모스트랜지스터와; 상기 각 피모스트랜지스터로부터 인가되는 전원전압을 내부를 관통하는 전원전압전달라인에 짝을 이루어 인가받고, 상기 각 엔모스트랜지스터로부터 인가되는 접지전위를 내부를 관통하는 접지전위전달라인에 상기와는 다르게 짝을 이루어 인가받는 다수의 4등분된 센스앰프어레이부로 센스앰프 구동회로를 구성하여 2층금속선을 통해 전원전압전달라인 및 접지전위전달라인의 다수지역에 전원전압 및 접지전위를 전달하여 전압강하 및 전류집중현상을 방지함과 아울러 센스앰프의 구동시간차를 개선함으로써, 고집적화를 꾀할 수 있는 효과와; 피모스트랜지스터 및 엔모스트랜지스터를 분리함으로써, 기판면적을 감소시킬수 있는 효과가 있다.

column12: Automatic spray deodorizing machine
column13: The utility model relates to an automatic spray deodorizing machine. When people enters an arc cover spray chamber and rotates once or twice, spray liquid with small particle size are sprayed from the spray discharge ports on the arc cover like water mist to contact clothes, thus the disgusting smell can be eliminated. A plurality of spray holes are arranged on the bottom board of the spray chamber in a ultrasonic humidifier, and a conventional ultrasonic vibration plate is arranged in a water storage room corresponding to the spray holes. A plurality of L-shaped conveying pipes are arranged between the arc cover with sensors arranged on both inner walls at the inlet and the cover of the ultrasonic humidifier. The upper ends of the L-shaped conveying pipes are communicated with the spray discharge ports of the arc cover, and the lower ends of the L-shaped conveying pipes are provided with a plurality of slots on a circumference and arranged on the spray ports of the bottom board. With the combined structure, large amount of spray liquid can be sprayed into the arc cover spray chamber just in one operation.

column12: SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING THE SAME
column13: PURPOSE: A semiconductor device and a method for manufacturing the same are provided to achieve the stable voltage of a plate node and to improve the leveling of the semiconductor device by reducing the step difference of the process. CONSTITUTION: A semiconductor device comprises bit lines(36a,36b), the first interlayer dielectric(35), a storage node(39), a dielectric layer(40), a plate node, a metal layer(42), and a wiring layer. The bit lines(36a,36b) is formed in the first impurity area(33c) of a transistor. The first interlayer dielectric(35) is formed in the entire surface of the semiconductor substrate(30) including the bit lines(36a,36b). A storage node(39) is formed in the second impurity area of the transistor formed in a cell area. A dielectric layer(40) is formed on an entire surface of the semiconductor substrate(30) including the storage node(39). A plate node is formed on the dielectric layer(40) in the cell area. A metal layer(42) is formed on the plate node. A wiring layer is provided to contact with the bit lines(36a,36b).

column12: RIDING DEVICE FOR CHILDREN
column13: The present invention relates to a riding device for children, capable of being transformed as a child grows. The riding device for children, according to one embodiment of the present invention, comprises: a frame extended from the front to the rear so as to support a front wheel and a rear wheel; a seat part mounted on the frame, restrained by the frame so as to be displaced between the front and the rear, and including a first part, and a second part separated from the first part; a side guide part provided at one side part of the frame, and including a first guide part for restraining the first part of the seat part so as to guide the seat part such that the seat part is displaced between the front and the rear, and a second guide part for guiding the first part such that the first part is displaced in one direction between the direction perpendicular to the ground and the tangential direction of a path along which the first part of the seat part moves from at least one position of the first guide part; and a rotating shaft for restraining the rotation of the second part of the seat part such that the seat part is pulled toward the rear when the first part of the seat part is displaced along the second guide part from at least one position of the first guide part.
column15: CHUNG BYONG CHON;;CHUNG JIN BUM

column12: VEHICLE DEVICE FOR CHILD
column13: The present invention relates to a riding device for a child which can change a shape thereof according to growth of a child. The riding device for a child according to an embodiment of the present invention comprises: a frame extended from a front side to a rear side to support a front wheel and a rear wheel; a seat unit which is loaded on the frame, is restrained on the frame to change a position thereof between the front side and the rear side, and comprises a first portion and a second portion separated from the first portion; a side guide unit which is disposed on one side of the frame, and comprises a first guide unit on which the first portion of the seat unit is restrained to guide the seat unit to change the position of the seat unit between the front side and the rear side, and a second guide unit to guide the first portion at one or more points of the first guide unit to change the position of the first portion in one direction between a tangential direction of a moving path of the first portion and a direction perpendicular to the ground; and a rotational shaft to restrain rotation of the second portion of the seat unit to bend the seat unit to the rear side when the first portion of the seat unit changes the position thereof at the one or more points of the first guide unit along the second guide unit.

column12: APPARATUS AND METHOD FOR PROVIDING DISCOUNT INFORMATION FOR ONLINE SHOPPING MALLS
column13: The present invention relates to a device for providing discount information for an online shopping mall which comprises: a menu identification unit identifying one menu selected by a user among a plurality of menus as a selection menu; and in response to the identification, a control unit displaying discount information corresponding to the selection menu on a screen of a user terminal and controlling a screen display of the user terminal according to an operation signal of the user. When the selection menu is a first menu for providing card discount information among the plurality of menus, the control unit generates a list including card discount information for each shopping mall, which is card discount information in progress at each of a plurality of online shopping malls, as a plurality of selection items and displays the list on the screen. In the selection items, information may be displayed which includes a set of card information of a discount card to which a discount is applied, card discount information containing discount rate information of the discount card, and shopping mall name information. Accordingly, convenience in purchasing products can be effectively increased.

column12: Classification system of dried sea cucumber using image analysis

To this end, the present invention comprises: an image photographing unit photographing sea cucumbers to obtain an image of the sea cucumbers; a visual image obtaining unit obtaining a three-dimensional image of the sea cucumbers based on the image obtained from the image photographing unit; a measurement unit calculating a surface area and a volume of the sea cucumbers obtained from the visual image obtaining unit; and a classification unit, wherein a ranking of the sea cucumbers based on the surface area and volume of the sea cucumbers is provided, and a hydration time to reach an optimum hydration rate in accordance with ranking of the sea cucumbers is stored.

column12: WIRELESS POWER RECEIVING APPARATUS FOR LOW HEAT AND METHOD THEREOF
column13: The present invention is to control the charge of a battery with low heat by receiving a wireless power signal transmitted from a wireless power transmission device. A control part controls an impedance matching/control part and matches impedance when a power receiving coil receives the wireless power signal. The control part determines the elapsed time of charging power at a power transmission device and the charge load condition of the power transmission device according to a current level detected by a current detection part. The generation of heat is minimized by selectively turning on a high heat generation transformation part and a low heat generation transformation part according to the determined charge load condition and the power transmission device is charged with electric power.

column12: TRANSFER METHOD FOR SEMICONDUCTOR PACKAGE OF SAWING SORTER SYSTEM
column13: A transfer method for a semiconductor package of a sawing sorter system is provided to load the semiconductor package even during the cut, store, transfer, test and sorting processes about the package, thereby overcoming the congestion completely. A sawing sorter system comprises a supply part(100), a test part(200) and a storage part(300). A first table(110) and a second table(120) included in the supply part are located adjacent to each other in a cross direction, and installed on transfer rails(111,121) respectively. A picker device(400) to pick up a semiconductor package(PKG) is installed on the transfer rails. The picker device respectively picks up and loads the package in a tray if the test is completed respectively. The test part judges the conformity and the unconformity of the package by performing various tests.

column13: The present invention relates to a plasticizer composition containing cyclodextrin derivatives, a flexible PVC composition with suppression of the migration of plasticizer containing this plasticizer composition, and a manufacturing method of the PVC composition. The manufacturing method includes the steps of: (Sl) preparing a cyclodextrin derivative, in which hydrogens of a cyclodextrin are substituted with a certain compound; (S2) mixing the cyclodextrin derivative, PVC and a low molecular weight liquid plasticizer to form a plastisol; and (S3) heating the plastisol into liquid and cooling the plastisol. This manufacturing method uses cyclodextrin derivatives, in which cyclodextrins are modified with certain compounds, and these derivatives form a complex with the low molecular weight liquid plasticizer to suppress plasticizer migration. column12: Plasticizer composition containing cyclodextrin derivatives, flexible PVC composition with suppression of the migration of plasticizer containing the same, and manufacturing method thereof
column13: The present invention relates to a plasticizer composition containing cyclodextrin derivatives, a flexible PVC composition with suppression of the migration of plasticizer containing this plasticizer composition, and a manufacturing method of the PVC composition. The manufacturing method includes the steps of: (S1) preparing a cyclodextrin derivative, in which hydrogens of a cyclodextrin are substituted with a certain compound; (S2) mixing the cyclodextrin derivative, PVC and a low molecular weight liquid plasticizer to form a plastisol; and (S3) heating the plastisol into liquid and cooling the plastisol. This manufacturing method uses cyclodextrin derivatives, in which cyclodextrins are modified with certain compounds, and these derivatives form a complex with the low molecular weight liquid plasticizer to suppress plasticizer migration. Thus, this method thereby allows mass-production of the flexible PVC with suppressed plasticizer migration in a simple and economical manner without using a solvent.

column12: Screen designing method and screen designing device providing a reduction of moire pattern
column13: A screen designing method and a screen designing device for reducing a moire pattern are provided. In the screen designing method, screen parameters corresponding to a preset screen frequency, a preset screen angle, and a preset resolution are detected first. Then, the coordinates of dot centers being the centers of cluster dots each with a plurality of microdots are detected. Next, a dot center order indicating a sequence in which the dot centers are turned on is determined. Thereafter, a microdot order indicating a sequence in which the microdots are turned on is determined using an evaluation function that quantitates the perception of a moiré pattern by a human's vision. Accordingly, the microdot order is determined using the evaluation function based on the visual characteristics of a human, thereby preventing patterns that degrade the quality of image formation and a moiré pattern from being generated.

column12: SCREEN DESIGN METHOD AND DEVICE, AND RECORDING MEDIUM
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a screen design method and device for reducing generation of moire patterns.

SOLUTION: The screen design method reduces generation of moire patterns, and is characterized by: a step 10 to detect screen parameters, corresponding to an established screen frequency, screen angle, and resolution; a step 12 to detect a coordinate of a dot center as the center of each cluster dot consisting of a plurality of microdots; a step 14 to determine the order of the dot center which indicates the order the dot center is turned on; and a step 16 to determine the order of the microdots which indicates the order the microdots are turned on, by using an evaluation function of a quantified recognition properties of human vision of the moire patterns. Thereby, the generation of the moire patterns and patterns which lower the image quality is prevented by determining the order of the microdots by using the evaluation function, based on human vision.

column12: SMART DOOR LOCK SYSTEM
column13: The prevent invention relates to a smart door lock system. The prevent invention provides a smart door lock system which communicates with a wireless network and interlinks with a security system, remotely opens/closes a door by a video call, and can improve security at the same time. For this, the present invention includes: a smart door lock which is installed on a door, detects a visitor approaching the door, photographs and stores an image according to a detection result, releases a lock when a first secret number and a second secret number inputted by a user are successively matched, and charges the lock when the lock is locked; a use terminal which remotely controls the lock/unlock of the smart door lock using a wired/wireless communications network, and communicates with the smart door lock using the video call; and a cloud server which receives the image photographed by the smart door lock and stores the same. By this configuration, the present invention can remotely control the door after a visitor is checked by the video call when the user is absent, can improve a monitoring function for intrusion, can improve security by preventing the secret number of the door lock from being easily released, can quickly cope with intrusion, and can improve the safety of a private life.

column12: ANTI-THEFT ARTICLE STORAGE DEVICE
column13: The purpose of the present invention is to provide an antitheft article storing device capable of basically blocking an article storing device from being opened by an outsider without intention, and allowing multiple article storing devices to be opened and closed by one security device. To achieve the purpose, the movable antitheft article storing device comprises: a base accommodating an article; a locking device fastening with the base by the locking device; and a security device separately formed from the locking device, electrically connected with the locking device, having a security number input unit, wherein the locking unit of the locking device can be opened and closed according to the number of the security number input unit. The antitheft article storing device of the present invention has a security device separately formed from the article storing device to separately store a security device. When the article storing device is moved to any place by other people, the security device is unlocked by a specialized tool and technology to basically prevent articles accommodated in the article accommodating device from being stolen. Further, the antitheft article storing device can reduce costs for manufacturing article storing devices as compared to the conventional art required to have security devices for each article storing device by controlling multiple article storing devices with one security device.

column12: BRAZING METHOD BETWEEN TITANIUM ALLOY AND STAINLESS STEEL
column13: The present invention relates to a brazing method for bonding dissimilar materials such as a titanium alloy and a stainless steel comprising: a step (a) for heating a Ni-based filler metal at 25-100°C which is over a melting point of the Ni-based filler metal after arranging the Ni-based filler metal on a binding part of a titanium alloy and a stainless steel; a first maintaining step (b) for maintaining the Ni-based filler metal for a fixed hour at 25-100°C which is over a melting point of the Ni-based filler metal; and a step (c) for cooling the Ni-based filler metal, and comprising a second maintaining step for maintaining a fixed temperature in heating of the (a) step. Especially, a melting point can be lowered by alloying between Ni and a titanium alloy since a Ni-based filler metal is used. Therefore, since diffusion between a titanium alloy and a stainless steel is promoted, sound brazing bonding can be performed. column12: Single electron transistor using porous silicon and manufacturing method thereof
column13: A single electron transistor using porous silicon, which is fabricated by applying porous silicon having a size of several tens of nanometers obtained by electrochemically etching silicon, and a fabrication method thereof, are provided. In the single electron transistor using porous silicon, silicon pores, each of which has a diameter of 5 nm or less, are fabricated by electrochemically etching a silicon on insulator (SOI) substrate having silicon dioxide (SiO _{ 2 } ) in its lower portion using an HF-based solution, and serve as islands of a single electron transistor. Also, a source and a drain are formed of silicon on which metal is deposited or silicon doped with impurities. Hence, formation of islands and tunnel barriers is easy, mass production is possible, and the sizes of islands can be controlled by oxidation, so that single electron transistors capable of operating at room temperature can be easily fabricated.

column12: CEMENT MORTAR COMPOSITE WITH WATER HOLDING CHARACTERICS USING ABSORBENT POLYMER AND MANUFACTURING METHOD OF BLOCK USING THE SAME
column13: A cement mortar composite with water holding characteristics using absorbent polymer is provided to secure finishing work time, to improve workability, bending of mortar, tension, a bonding strength and durability capacity. The absorbent polymer comprises ethylene vinyl acetate redispersible powder resin, starch and polyacrylamide and inorganic pigment. The cement binder comprises normal portland cement 50~75 weight%, blast furnace slag 5~25 weight% and alumina silicate pozzolanic material 5~20 weight% based on the absorbent polymer 100 weight%.

column12: Method of producing 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2h-dibenzofuran-1-one
column13: Disclosed is a process of producing 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-one, and 1-hydroxydibenzofuran and 4-hydroxycarbazole using 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-one as an intermediate. 2-chlorocyclohexanone and 1,3-cyclohexanedione are reacted with each other in a base and organic solvent to form a carbon-carbon bond, and then subject to a cyclization reaction in the presence of an acid solution to produce 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-one. 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-one as the intermediate is subjected to nitrogen substitution and dehydrogenation reactions to produce 4-hydroxycarbazole. 1-hydroxydibenzofuran is produced by dehydrogenating 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-one. The process according to the present invention is advantageous in that a low-priced starting material is used to improve economic efficiency, the reaction is stable in specific base and organic solvent conditions, and 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-one is produced at high yield because of the cyclization reaction in the presence of the acid solution. Furthermore, 1-hydroxydibenzofuran and 4-hydroxycarbazole can be stably and economically produced using the above intermediate.

column12: METHOD FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SERINOL
column13: Disclosed is a method for preparing serinol (2-amino-1,3-proanediol). From nitromethane, para-formaldehyde and sodium hydroxide, 1-nitro-1,3-propanediol sodium salt is prepared as a medical intermediate. In a fixed bed, this intermediate is allowed to undergo the continuous hydrogenation of 2-nitro-1,3-propanediol sodium salt and methanol as shown in reaction (1). In addition to being simple, the method is economically favorable and affords the high yield and high purity of serinol.

column12: SEMICONDUCTOR PACKAGE AND MANUFACTURING METHOD THEREOF
column13: The present invention relates to a semiconductor package and a manufacturing method thereof, to form a fine conductive pattern of a thin film on an upper surface of a metal substrate and resin through electroplating by using the metal substrate as a seed to realize a fine pitch. According to the present invention, the semiconductor package comprises: a substrate which includes a metal substrate having multiple lands arranged and separated from each other, resin interposed between the multiple lands, and multiple conductive patterns formed on an upper surface of each land to be electrically connected to the land; a semiconductor die electrically connected to an upper surface of the conductive patterns; and an encapsulant to encapsulate the substrate and the semiconductor die, and to expose a lower surface of the substrate to the outside. The substrate has a step formed between a lower surface of the multiple lands and a lower surface of the resin.

column12: METHOD OF PREPARING 10H-DIBENZO[b,f]]1,4]THIAZEPIN-11-ONE
column13: Disclosed is a method of preparing 10H-dibenzo⏧b,f]⏧1,4]thiazepin-11-one, including reacting dithiosalicylic acid with 1-chloro-2-nitrobenzene in a basic aqueous solution in the presence of absence of a reducing agent, to prepare 2-(2-nitrophenylsulfuryl)benzoic acid; subjecting the 2-(2-nitrophenylsulfuryl)benzoic acid to nitro group reduction in the presence of hydrogen, a solvent and a heterogeneous metal catalyst, to prepare 2-(2-aminophenylsulfuryl)benzoic acid; and directly cyclizing the 2-(2-aminophenylsulfuryl)benzoic acid in an organic solvent in the presence or absence of an acid catalyst. column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR SIMULATING REALTIME SEVERE ACCIDENT PHENOMENA FOR TRAINING SIMULATOR OF THE NUCLEAR POWER PLANT
column13: The present invention relates to a system and a method for simulating real time severe accidents of a simulator for training in a nuclear power plant. The purpose of the present invention is to provide a system and a method for simulating real time severe accidents in a simulated target nuclear power plant at a simulator for training in a nuclear power plant by using MAAP5TM as a code commonly used to analyze severe accidents in a nuclear power plant. The present invention, to achieve the purpose, comprises a simulator server driven to simulate all systems of a reference nuclear power plant and providing a dynamic value for the simulation of a target nuclear power plant; a database construction part extracting information about global variables of a severe accident analysis code and constructing a database; a global database part storing the information about the global variables of the severe accident analysis code; a simulation execution part simulating real time severe accidents; and a global memory part storing current values of all global variables registered in the global database part. column12: NON-VOLATILE MEMORY DEVICE WITH QUANTUM DOT AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING THE SAME
column13: PURPOSE: A nonvolatile memory device and a manufacturing method thereof are provided to improve a coupling ratio by increasing the capacitance of the inter-gate dielectric structure. CONSTITUTION: A floating gate(120) is formed on a tunneling layer. An inter-gate dielectric structure is comprised by successively stacking a first silicon oxide layer, a dielectric layer, and a second silicon oxide layer on a floating gate. A control gate(140) is formed on the inter-gate dielectric structure. A high dielectric layer includes a fist high dielectric layer and a second high dielectric layer which are stacked. The density of the electron trap site of the first high dielectric layer is smaller than that of the second high dielectric layer. The energy band gap or conductive band-offset of the first dielectric layer is larger than that of the second high dielectric layer.

column12: METHOD FOR PRODUCING 1-[CYANO(p-METHOXYPHENYL)ETHYL]CYCLOHEXANOL
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a method for producing 1-[cyano(p-methoxyphenyl)ethyl]cyclohexanol, capable of producing the 1-[cyano(p-methoxyphenyl)ethyl]cyclohexanol comprising an important intermediate which is used for producing venlafaxine having high effect as an antidepressant economically with high purity, and capable of industrially mass-producing the product as well.

SOLUTION: This method comprises comprises together reacting p-methoxyphenylacetonitrile and cyclohexanone in the presence of a mixed solvent of an aqueous solution of a basic substance and a water-soluble alcohol, while stirring, so as to obtain solid particles, and then filtering the obtained particles, so as to obtain the 1-[cyano(p-methoxyphenyl)ethyl]cyclohexanol expressed by formula 1.

column12: Method for fabricating semiconductor package having multi-layer encapsulated conductive substrate and structure
column13: A method for fabricating a semiconductor package having a multi-layer encapsulated conductive substrate and a structure are disclosed. In one embodiment, the semiconductor package includes a multi-layer encapsulated conductive substrate having a fine pitch. The multi-layer encapsulated conductive substrate includes a conductive leads spaced apart from each other, a first encapsulant disposed between the leads, a first conductive layer electrically connected to the plurality of leads, conductive pillars disposed on the first conductive layer, a second encapsulant encapsulating the first conductive layer and the conductive pillars, and a second conductive layer electrically connected to the conductive pillars and exposed in the second encapsulant. column12: PROCESSES FOR PREPARING 3,4,5,7,8,9-HEXAHYDRO-2H-DIBENZOFURAN-1-ON WITH IMPROVED YIELD, AND 1-HYDROXYDIBENZOFURAN AND 4-HYDROXYCARBAZOLE USING THE SAME COMPOUND AS INTERMEDIATE WITH IMPROVED STABILITY AND REDUCED COST
column13: PURPOSE: Processes for preparing 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-on, and 1-hydroxydibenzofuran and 4-hydroxycarbazole using the same compound as an intermediate are provided, thereby improving the yield of 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-on, and stably and cheaply preparing 1-hydroxydibenzofuran and 4-hydroxycarbazole with a cheap and stable starting material. CONSTITUTION: The process for preparing 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-on of the formula(3) comprises the steps of: (a) reacting 2-chlorocyclohexanon of the formula(1) with 1,3-cyclohexandion of the formula(2) in base and organic solvent to form a carbon-carbon bond at 0 to 150 deg. C for 1 to 6 hours; and (b) cyclization of the reaction product in the presence of acid solution, wherein the base is potassium carbonate; the organic solvent is acetone, methylethylketone, methylisobutylketone and a mixture thereof; and the acid solution is hydrochloric acid, sulfuric acid, phosphoric acid, nitric acid or acetic acid. The process for preparing 1-hydroxydibenzofuran of the formula(5) comprises the steps of: (a) preparing 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-on of the formula(3); and (b) dehydrogenating the 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-on of the formula(3) in the presence of high boiling point of solvent and metallic catalyst. The process for preparing 4-hydroxycarbazole of the formula(6) comprises the steps of: (a) preparing 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-on of the formula(3); (b) substituting oxygen in the 3,4,5,7,8,9-hexahydro-2H-dibenzofuran-1-on of the formula(3) with nitrogen using ammonia or ammonia water to prepare 1,2,3,5,6,7,8,9-octahydrocarbazol-4-on of the formula(4); and (c) dehydrogenating the 1,2,3,5,6,7,8,9-octahydrocarbazol-4-on of the formula(4) in the presence of high boiling point of solvent and metallic catalyst.

column12: NONVOLATILE MEMORY DEVICES AND METHODS OF MANUFACTURING THE SAME
column13: Nonvolatile memory devices and related methods of manufacturing the same are provided. A nonvolatile memory device includes a tunneling layer on a substrate, a floating gate on the tunneling layer, an inter-gate dielectric layer structure on the floating gate, and a control gate on the inter-gate dielectric layer structure. The inter-gate dielectric layer structure includes a first silicon oxide layer, a high dielectric layer on the first silicon oxide layer, and a second silicon oxide layer on the high dielectric layer opposite to the first silicon oxide layer The high dielectric layer may include first and second high dielectric layers laminated on each other, and the first high dielectric layer may have a lower density of electron trap sites than the second high dielectric layer and may have a larger energy band gap or conduction band-offset than the second high dielectric layer.

column12: FIRE RESISTANCE WALLPAPER AND MANUFACTURING METHOD THEREOF
column13: The present invention relates to a flame retardant wallpaper and a method for producing the same. When a base material consisting of combustible substances is combusted in case of fire, aluminum hydroxide is pyrolyzed to generate water, and bentonite absorbs the water, so that the volume thereof is increased and the surface area thereof is also increased by means of interlayer expansion. Accordingly, pyrolysis is delayed, and an extinguishing function can be ensured. To realize this, the flame retardant wallpaper of the present invention comprises: a base layer (110); a foaming layer (120) laminated on the top of the base layer (110) and including aluminum hydroxide and bentonite in a polyvinyl chloride resin; and a print layer (130) laminated on the top of the foaming layer (120). By means of the present invention, when the base layer consisting of combustible substances is combusted in case of fire, aluminum hydroxide is pyrolyzed to generate water, and bentonite absorbs the water, so that the volume thereof is increased and the surface area thereof is also increased by means of interlayer expansion. Accordingly, pyrolysis is delayed. Also, an extinguishment function can be ensured by means of dehydration above a particular temperature.

column12: METHOD FOR THE PRODUCTION OF SERINOL
column13: Disclosed is a method for preparing serinol (2-amino-1,3-proanediol). From nitromethane, para-formaldehyde and sodium hydroxide, 1-nitro-1,3-propanediol sodium salt is prepared as a medical intermediate. In a fixed bed, this intermediate is allowed to undergo the continuous hydrogenation of 2-nitro-1,3-propanediol sodium salt and methanol as shown in reaction (I). In addition to being simple, the method is economically favorable and affords the high yield and high purity of serinol.

column12: IMAGE PROCESSING METHOD AND IMAGE PROCESSING APPARATUS USING HYBRID LOOK-UP TABLE
column13: An image processing method using a hybrid look-up table and an image processing apparatus are provided to prevent an artifact like a blurring or a mosaic pattern by applying a look-up table corresponding to a characteristic of an image. A storing unit(120) stores the first multi-bit pixel value and the second multi-bit pixel value designated by a bit pattern formed from states of pixels of a binary image in a memory table. A converting unit(130) assigns one, specified by the bit pattern corresponding to the states of the pixels in an image block of the binary image including binary pixels corresponding to pixels of a multi-bit pixel image, between the first multi-bit pixel value and the second multi-bit pixel value to the pixels of the multi-bit pixel image. When the pixel block has the first pixel context, the converting unit assigns the first multi-bit pixel value to the pixels. When the pixel block has the second pixel context, the converting unit assigns the second multi-bit pixel value to the pixels.

column12: ILLUMINATING DEVICE FOR DISPLAY APPARATUS, BACKLIGHT UNIT INCLUDING THE SAME AND LIQUID CRYSTAL DISPLAY USING THE BACKLIGHT UNIT
column13: An illuminating apparatus for a display device and a backlight unit, and an LCD(Liquid Crystal Display) including the same are provided to form a pattern to a reflection layer, thereby diffusing or scattering the light with the uniform illumination. Upper and lower substrates are arranged separately and oppositely with each other. An anode electrode is formed at the lower surface of the upper substrate. A fluorescent layer is formed at the lower surface of the anode electrode. A cathode electrode is formed at the upper surface of the lower substrate. An electron emission source is formed on the cathode electrode. A reflection layer is separately arranged between the electron emission source and the fluorescent layer. A pattern is formed at the surface of the reflection layer toward the fluorescent layer in order to diffuse the light beam emitted from the fluorescent layer.

column12: Image processing using hybrid lookup table
column13: An image processing method and an image processing apparatus converts a binary image into a grayscale image by increasing the size and information quantity of the binary image. The image processing method includes generating a plurality of lookup tables having multiple gray level values assigned to a predetermined pattern of the binary image such that the gray level is retrieved from the plurality of lookup tables depending on the context of the block being processed. The binary image may be converted into the grayscale image by applying the gray value of one of the plurality of lookup tablesthat corresponds to the context, such as the frequency components of the binary image. With this configuration, since the size and information quantity of an image can be reduced for transmission, itis possible to prevent deterioration of image quality when the image is restored, while also printing at a higher speed.

column12: BRAZING METHOD BETWEEN MOLIBDENUM AND TITANIUM ALLOY
column13: The present invention relates to a method for brazing heterogeneous molybdenum and titanium alloys. The present invention includes (a) a first heating step in which an Ag-Cu-based filler metal is arranged at a bonding portion of the molybdenum and titanium alloys, heating is performed up to 25°C to 100°C under the melting point of the Ag-Cu-based filler metal, and the state is maintained for a predetermined period of time; (b) a secondary heating step in which heating is performed up to 25°C to 100°C over the melting point of the Ag-Cu-based filler metal in the first heating step and the state is maintained for a predetermined period of time; and (c) a cooling step in which the Ag-Cu-based filler metal is cooled. According to the present invention, the melting point is much lower than the phase transformation temperature of Ti and Ti wettability is excellent, and thus no phase transformation is caused in the Ti alloy and sound brazing bonding is possible.

column12: METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR MONITORING FOREST FIRE
column13: A forest fire monitoring method and system are provided to exactly detect a forest fire and to quickly cope with a forest fire by informing a manager's terminal of the forest fire. A forest fire monitoring and informing method is composed of steps of: storing sensing information transmitted from a sensor unit and image data received from an image obtaining unit through the wire or wireless network(610); judging whether the present time corresponds to a pre-set daytime range or not; determining that a forest fire breaks out if a grey region of the image data analyzed through RGB(Red,Green,Blue) analysis algorisms is over a predetermined critical regional area, when the present time corresponds to a pre-set daytime range and determining that a forest fire occurs if an ignition region of the image data analyzed through HSV(Hue Saturation Value) analysis algorisms is over a predetermined critical regional area, when the present time does not correspond to a pre-set daytime range; and generating emergency information by using the sensing information and transmitting the emergency information to a predetermined receiving terminal(625,630).

column12: SEMICONDUCTOR PACKAGE AND MANUFACTURING METHOD THEREOF
column13: The present invention relates to a semiconductor package and a manufacturing method thereof. An objective of the present invention is to reduce the coefficient of mutual induction between a substrate and an inductor by positioning an inductor disposed on a semiconductor die to the top of a puddle so as to increase the separation distance between the substrate and the inductor, and to improve the heat dissipation performance by exposing the die pad of the substrate to the bottom surface of the substrate. To this end, the present invention discloses a semiconductor package and a manufacturing method thereof, wherein the semiconductor package includes: a substrate including a die pad having a rectangular plate shape, a lead frame having a plurality of lands spaced apart from each side of the die pad, and a substrate encapsulant interposed between the die pad and the plurality of lands; a semiconductor die electrically connected to the die pad and the lands; and an encapsulant encapsulating the substrate and the semiconductor die, wherein the substrate bottom surface is exposed to the outside. The top surface of the die pad is provided with a puddle having a certain depth downwards.

column12: Lead frame for manufacturing semiconductor package and method for manufacturing the same
column13: The present invention relates to a semiconductor package and a method of manufacturing the same, and more particularly, to a new semiconductor package capable of reducing thermal stress in a semiconductor package manufacturing process and a method of manufacturing the same. That is, the present invention is to improve the structure of a chip mounting board in which a semiconductor chip is grounded and attached by a conductive connecting unit. In the area of the top surface of the chip mounting board, a concave portion is formed between regions to be grounded by the conductive connecting unit. So, the area for the upper surface of the chip mounting plate can be reduced. The thermal stress acting on the upper surface of the chip mounting plate in the package manufacturing process can be reduced.

column12: IMAGE PROCESSING USING HYBRID LOOKUP TABLE
column13: An image processing method and an image processing apparatus converts a binary image into a grayscale image by increasing the size and information quantity of the binary image. The image processing method includes generating a plurality of lookup tables having multiple gray level values assigned to a predetermined pattern of the binary image such that the gray level is retrieved from the plurality of lookup tables depending on the context of the block being processed. The binary image may be converted into the grayscale image by applying the gray value of one of the plurality of lookup tables that corresponds to the context, such as the frequency components of the binary image. With this configuration, since the size and information quantity of an image can be reduced for transmission, it is possible to prevent deterioration of image quality when the image is restored, while also printing at a higher speed.

column12: Apparatus for generating seek direction detecting signal for optical pickup
column13: An apparatus for generating a seek direction detecting signal for an optical pickup for determining the relative position of the center of an optical spot focused on an optical disk with respect to the center of a disk track, is disclosed. The apparatus focuses a main beam and a sub-beam having a predetermined aberration in the radial direction on a track of the optical disk by a light dividing unit. The main beam is focused on a first optical detector (25), and the sub-beam is focused on a second optical detector (27) neighboring the first optical detector (25). The second optical detector (27) is divided into three or four portions in a direction corresponding to the radial direction of the optical disk, is divided into two portions in a direction corresponding to the tangential direction of the optical disk, has six or eight separate areas. The portions of the second optical detector (27) receive the portions of the sub-beam and convert the received optical signals into electrical signals independently. A signal processing portion includes a first signal processing portion (30) for summing and differentiating the signals output from the first optical detector (25), and for detecting a track error signal; and a second signal processing portion (40) for generating a seek direction detecting signal from the signals detected by the second optical detector (27).

column12: POWER TRANSMISSION APPARATUS FOR A COMPRESSOR
column13: PURPOSE: A power transmission of a compressor is provided to improve the torsional durability and the strength of a limiter by adding nickel, molybdenum, and copper etc. CONSTITUTION: A power transmission of a compressor comprises a pulley(10), a damper(40), a limiter(50), and a hub(60). The pulley is rotated by the torque of an engine. The damper absorbs the impact caused by torque transferred by the rotary shaft of a compressor by being rotated by the pulley. The limiter prevents the transferring of the torque of an engine to the rotary shaft larger than predetermined level by being broken. The hub transfers the torque of the limiter to the rotary shaft by being connected to the limiter and the rotary shaft. The limiter is composed of 0.1 to 0.7 wt.% of Ni, 0.1 to 0.7 wt.% of Mo, and residual Fe.

column13: The present invention relates to a frame system of a building using a PC-column integrated with a cantilever in a precast concrete (PC) column, comprising: a vertical part which is configured in a height of one story or a plurality of stories of a building and forms a body of the column; and a horizontal part which is horizontally protruding to a certain length to both sides of the vertical part and to a height corresponding to each story of the building. The vertical part and the horizontal part are fabricated by being integrally combined while having reinforcing bars therein. A frame system of a building using a PC-column integrated with a cantilever comprises: a PC-column integrated with a cantilever which is installed at a planned position at a certain interval and has the vertical part and the horizontal part; a PC girder to which both end parts of mutually opposing horizontal parts of an adjoining PC-column integrated with a cantilever are coupled; and a PC slab which is installed in an upper part of the PC-column integrated with a cantilever and the PC girder. After placing reinforcing bars in an upper part of the PC girder and the PC slab, toppling concrete is poured.

column12: Field emission display device and field emission type backlight device having a sealing structure for vacuum exhaust
column13: A field emission display device and a field emission type backlight device having a sealing structure for a vacuum exhaust are provided. The field emission display device is constructed with a cathode substrate and an anode substrate attached to each other and facing each other and a vacuum-exhausted panel space formed therebetween to generated a visual image. Also, the field emission display device is constructed with a sealing member disposed along edges of the cathode substrate and the anode substrate to seal the panel space. At least one inlet exposed to the panel space and an exhaust passage through which the inlet communicates with an outside of the field emission display device are formed in the sealing member. The field emission display device and the field emission type backlight device according to the present invention has a reduced number of manufacturing processes and is suitable for a compact, slim and lightweight design, and a large screen by having the sealing structure for the vacuum exhaust.

column12: WIRE-BONDING METHOD AND SEMICONDUCTOR PACKAGE FORMED BY USING THE METHOD
column13: Provided are a wire-bonding method and a semiconductor package formed by using the method. The wire-bonding method can improve process speed by forming a bonding ball just once and then performing a stitch bonding when a wire for successively connecting at least three connection terminals is formed. Also, defect frequency can be reduced by reducing the number of bonding balls formed. Thereby, provided is a semiconductor package having improved reliability.

column12: METHODS FOR THE REGENERATION OF TITANIUM-CONTAINING MOLECULAR SIEVE CATALYSTS
column13: A method which can regenerate the catalyst easily and can stably maintain activity of a regenerated catalyst equal to that of a new catalyst for a long time by treating a deactivation-proceeded titanium containing molecular sieve catalyst with a specific mixed solvent is provided. The method for regenerating a titanium-containing molecular sieve catalyst comprises the steps of: (i) washing residual reactanta and impurities by pretreating the catalyst with water or alcohol when a titanium containing molecular sieve catalyst used in the epoxidation reaction of an olefin compound is deactivated; and (ii) contacting the pretreated catalyst with a mixed solution of water and alcohol to perform regeneration of the catalyst. The method further comprises the step of additionally washing and drying the regenerated catalyst with water or alcohol after the catalyst regenerating step(ii). The alcohol is selected from the group consisting of C1 to C10 alcohols. The titanium-containing molecular sieve catalyst is a titanium-containing molecular sieve catalyst comprising silicalite.

column12: Method of aging field emission devices

column12: NON-HYDRATION STRENGTH IN CEMENTITIOUS COMPOSITIONS
column13: Described are compositions and methods for controlled strength development in a hydratable cementitious material, and more particularly to the use of polymerizable monomer components, which are initiated and activated by a redox pair which are mixed in controlled fashion, for enhancing non-hydration strength within the matrix of the plastic hydratable cementitious material before setting of the cementitious material begins. Exemplary applications include minimizing pressures on formwork for high fluid ready-mix applications, enhancing support and bonding properties for integrated concrete slab work and other sequential applications, or facilitating speedy 3D printing applications, among other unique possibilities.

column12: Polyurethane fabric for airbag pad and manufacturing method thereof
column13: The invention provides polyurethane fabric for airbag pads, which serves as fabric of airbag pads having coating agents coated on the surface of textiles. The coating agents are formed through polyurethane combination of more than one polyhydric alcohol selected from polyhydric alcohol groups and more than one isocranate selected from two isocranate groups. The manufacturing method includes a combination step (S110) in while the polyhydric alcohol and the isocranate are mixed inside a reaction container; a polyurethane combination step (S120) in which the mixed polyhydric alcohol and isocranate is heated to form polyurethane combination so as to make polyurethane coating agents; an additive mixing step (S130) in which at least one of the fire retardant, the smoothing agent or the antioxygen agent is mixed in the polyurethane coating agents; a polyurethane coating step (S140) in which polyurethane coating agents are coated on the surfaces of textiles; and a polyurethane drying step (S150) in which the coated polyurethane coating agents are dried.

column12: CONTINUOUS PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF OPTICALLY PURE (S)-beta HYDROXY-gamma-BUTYROLACTONE
column13: Disclosed is a continuous process for the production of optically pure (S)-&bgr;-hydroxy-᜼-butyrolactone having constantly maintained optical activity, consisting of hydrogenating 2-50 wt% of a substituted carboxylic acid derivative in a solvent using a fixed bed reactor filled with a precious metal catalyst-impregnated inorganic oxide carrier at 50-500 °C under pressure of 15-5,500 psig at weight-space-velocity of 0.1-10 h-1, in which a molar ratio of hydrogen to carboxylic acid derivative ranges from 2 to 10. The desired material can be produced in higher optical purity and at higher yield by the current process which is relatively simpler and environmentally safer than conventional processes. Additionally, increased production efficiency leads to production of the desired material on a large scale.

column12: METHOD OF COMMUNICATING MULTI INPUT MULTI OUTPUT AND SYSTEM USING THE SAME
column13: A multiple input/output communications method and a multiple input/output communications system using the same are provided to maximize data transfer rate by allocating non-selection beam forming vector to a non-selection user by using channel quality information. A selection beam foaming vector decision unit(310) determines a selection beam foaming vector corresponding to the selected user based on the channel quality information fed back from a plurality of users. The selection beam foaming vector decision unit determines a selection beam forming vector through a PU2RC(Per User Unitary Rate Control) technique. In case of assigning non-selection beam forming vector by using the channel quality information, the performance information generator(320) produces the capability information. The channel vector estimating unit(321) estimates the channel vector corresponding to non-selection user based on the channel quality information. A capability information calculation unit(322) calculates the capability information by using the channel vector.

column12: DRIED SEA CUCUMBER MANUFACTURING METHOD USING FA INFRARED RADIATION DRYING.
column13: The present invention relates to a method for making a dried sea cucumber using far-infrared radiation, and more specifically, the purpose of the present invention is to provide optimal far-infrared intensity, temperature, flow rate, moisture diffusion coefficient, and activation energy in making the dried sea cucumber using far-infrared radiation. The method for making a dried sea cucumber using far-infrared radiation according to the present invention can shorten the drying time, minimize the denaturation due to heat, reduce the energy consumption, improve the quality of the dried sea cucumber, and decrease the production cost, when compared with the method for making a dried sea cucumber through hot-air drying of a prior art.

column12: METHOD FOR FABRICATING THE CI(G)S THIN-FILM WITH DENSE MICROSTRUCTURE USING STOICHIOMETRIC CI(G)S PARTICLES CONTAINING PHASES WITH LOW MELTING POINT
column13: PURPOSE: A method for fabricating a CI(G)S thin-film is provided to prepare a film with excellent density including low melting point CuSe and CuSe2 binary phase through an inexpensive process and to control the stoichiometric ratio of Cu : In : Se without a separate additional process. CONSTITUTION: A method for fabricating a CI(G)S thin-film comprises the steps of: (i) mixing a copper compound, an indium compound and a selenium compound with a reaction solvent having the boiling point of 200 °C or greater; (ii) irradiating microwaves to the mixed solution and performing the reaction at 200~300 °C for 15~40 minutes to prepare CI(G)S particles in which CuSe and CuSe2 are formed; and (iii) applying CI(G)S particles to a substrate and heating the coated material to prepare the CI(G)S thin-film.

The method for manufacturing a semiconductor package comprises: a first conductive pattern forming step of forming a first conductive pattern on a first surface of a carrier; a first conductive filler forming step of forming a first conductive filler on the first conductive pattern to be electrically connected; a first encapsulation step of encapsulating the first conductive pattern and the first conductive filler with a first encapsulant; a second conductive pattern forming step of forming a second conductive pattern on the first conductive filler, which is exposed to the outside of the first encapsulant, to electrically be connected; a second conductive filler forming step of forming a second conductive filler on a part of the second conductive pattern to be electrically formed; a second encapsulation step of forming a reception space allowing the remaining part of the second conductive pattern to be exposed and encapsulating the part of the second conductive pattern and the second conductive filler with a second encapsulant; and a first semiconductor die arranging step of arranging a first semiconductor die in the reception space to electrically be connected to the second conductive pattern exposed to the outside of the second encapsulant.

column12: Continuous process for the production of optically pure (S)- beta-hydroxy-gamma-butyrolactone
column13: Disclosed is a process for the production of optically pure (S)-beta-hydroxy-gamma-butyrolactone through the hydrogenation of substituted carboxylic acid derivatives. A solution containing 1 to 50% by weight of a substituted carboxylic acid derivative is fed at a WHSV of 0.1 to 10 h ¹ , to a fixed bed reactor which is filled with a catalyst and maintained at a reaction temperature of 50 to 550 C. under a halogen partial pressure of 15 to 5,500 psig. The catalyst is composed of a noble metal as a catalytically effective ingredient which is impregnated in an inorganic oxide as a support. The molar ratio of the hydrogen to the substituted carboxylic acid derivative is maintained at a molar ratio of 1:1 to 10:1. The process can produce optically pure (S)-beta-hydroxy-gamma-butyrolactone with higher purities at higher yields than can conventional techniques. In addition to being relatively simple and environmentally friendly, the process is so economically favorable as to apply to industrial production.

column12: Method for fabricating semiconductor package having a multi-layer molded conductive substrate and structure
column13: In one embodiment, a method for fabricating a semiconductor package includes providing a multi-layer molded conductive structure. The multi-layer molded conductive structure includes a first conductive structure disposed on a surface of a carrier and a first encapsulant covering at least portions of the first conductive structure while other portions are exposed in the first encapsulant. A second conductive structure is disposed on the first encapsulant and electrically connected to the first conductive structure. A second encapsulant covers a first portion of the second conductive structure while a second portion of the second conductive structure is exposed to the outside, and a third portion of the second conductive structure is exposed in a receiving space disposed in the second encapsulant. The method includes electrically connecting a semiconductor die to the second conductive structure and in some embodiments removing the carrier.

column12: PACKAGING AND INTERCONNECT SYSTEM FOR INTEGRATED CIRCUITS
column13: A thin MCM packaging structure (10) and technique is provided in which a thin film decal interconnect circuit (16) is fabricated on a thin aluminum wafer (22). The thin film decal interconnect (16) employs AU metallurgy for bonding and comprises a bond pad/ground plane layer, topside pads, and one or more routing layers. The top routing layer also acts as the pad layer along the edge of the interconnect structure (16). The underside of the decal interconnect structure (16) is provided with metal pads for attachment to conventional aluminum or gold I/O pads on one surface of the integrated circuit die (12). A thermosonic bonding system is used to bond the die pads (66) to the pads. The aluminum wafer is selectively removed forming one or more cavities (18, 20) to hold one or more die (12, 14) to be mounted on the MCM structure (10). The dies (12, 14) are oriented with their pads (66, 70) in contact with contact pads on the thin film decal interconnect (16) to which they are bonded and cavities (18, 20) are filled with a liquid encapsulant (26) and cured. A lead frame has inner bond leads electrically bonded to bonding pads (122) of the thin film multilayer interconnect circuit disposed about periphery thereof and a multilayer laminate board is mechanically bonded over the thin film multilayer interconnect circuit (16) and over the inner bond leads of the lead frame (120) and has a first layer (124) including conductive pads (130) extending outward from about an inner periphery thereof, and a second layer including apertures (136) aligned with outwardly extending portions of the conductive pads (130).

column12: CONTINUOUS PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF OPTICALLY PURE (S)-BETA HYDROXY-GAMMA-BUTYROLACTONE
column13: Disclosed is a continuous process for the production of optically pure (S)-beta-hydroxy-gamma-butyrolactone having constantly maintained optical activity, consisting of hydrogenating 2-50 wt % of a substituted carboxylic acid derivative in a solvent using a fixed bed reactor filled with a precious metal catalyst-impregnated inorganic oxide carrier at 50-500° C. under pressure of 15-5,500 psig at weight-space-velocity of 0.1-10 h<SUP>-1</SUP>, in which a molar ratio of hydrogen to carboxylic acid derivative ranges from 2 to 10. Additionally, increased production efficiency leads to production of the desired material on a large scale.

column12: PROCEDIMIENTO CONTINUO DE PRODUCCION DE (S)-BETA)-HIDROXI-GAMMA-BUTIROLACTONA OPTICAMENTE PURA.
column13: Un procedimiento para producir(S)-beta-hidroxi- gamma-butirolactona ópticamente pura a partir de un derivado de ácido carboxílico sustituido mediante hidrogenación, caracterizado porque: en dicha hidrogenación, una disolución que contiene del 1 al 50% en peso del derivado de ácido carboxílico sustituido se suministra a una WHSV de 0, 1 a 10 h-1, a un reactor de lecho fijo el cual se carga con un catalizador y se mantiene a una temperatura de reacción de 50 a 550ºC bajo una presión parcial de hidrógeno de 103.421, 4 a 37.921, 2 x 103 pascales manométricos (15 a 5.500 psig), teniendo dicho catalizador un metal noble como un ingrediente efectivo catalíticamente y un óxido inorgánico como un soporte, manteniéndose dicho hidrógeno a una razón molar de 1:1 a 10:1 relativa al derivado de ácido carboxílico sustituido, y en que dicho derivado de ácido carboxílico sustituido es de la fórmula: en la que R es alquilo lineal que contiene de 1 a 10 átomos de carbono, tales como grupo metilo, etilo o n-propilo, un cicloalquilo, o un arilo; y R¿ es un átomo de hidrógeno o un metilo.

column12: METHOD OF MANUFACTURING FIELD EMISSION DEVICE
column13: A method for manufacturing a field emission device is provided to improve the uniformity of luminance by accurately forming an emitter at a center portion of an emitter hole. A cathode electrode(112), an insulation layer(114) and a gate material layer are formed on a substrate(110), and then a metal sacrificial layer is formed on the gate material layer. A through-hole is formed in the metal sacrificial layer and the gate material layer to expose the insulation layer. An emitter hole(130) is formed in the exposed insulation layer to expose the cathode electrode, and then the gate material layer is etched to form a gate electrode(115). An emitter(150) made of carbon nano-tubes is formed on the cathode electrode.

column12: CONTINUOUS PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF OPTICALLY PURE (S)- beta -HYDROXY- gamma -BUTYROLACTONE
column13: Disclosed is a process for the production of optically pure (S)-beta-hydroxy-gamma-butyrolactone through the hydrogenation of substituted carboxylic acid derivatives. A solution containing 1 to 50 % by weight of a substituted carboxylic acid derivative is fed at a WHSV of 0.1 to 10 h-1, to a fixed bed reactor which is filled with a catalyst and maintained at a reaction temperature of 50 to 550 °C under a halogen partial pressure of 15 to 5,500 psig. The catalyst is composed of a noble metal as a catalytically effective ingredient which is impregnated in an inorganic oxide as a support. The molar ratio of the hydrogen to the substituted carboxylic acid derivative is maintained at a molar ratio of 1:1 to 10:1. The process can produce optically pure (S)-beta-hydroxy-gamma-butyrolactone with higher purities at higher yields than can conventional techniques. In addition to being relatively simple and environmentally friendly, the process is so economically favorable as to apply to industrial production.

column12: Lightproof water soluble resin composite
column13: The present invention provides a water-soluble resin composition which can be used as a light-proofness protecting film arranged between an organic semiconductor film and an interlayer insulating film. The light-proofness protecting film can prevent the crystallinity of the organic electrical components from reducing when the organic semiconductor film of the organic electrical component contact with the interlayer insulating film, besides, the light-proofness protecting film also can solve the problem that the interlayer insulating film is photo-oxidized when exposed to light. The present invention relates to a light-proofness water-soluble resin composition, particular to a light-proofness water-soluble resin composition containing : a) water-soluble resin, b) water-soluble dye compound, c) solvents ,and the light-proofness water-soluble resin composition is used as protecting films for organic semiconductors.

column12: Evaluation method of fine-dust removal rate on the fabric surface
column13: The present invention relates to an evaluation method of a removal rate of fine dust adsorbed on a fabric surface. According to the present invention, the evaluation method of the removal rate of fine dust adsorbed on the fabric surface comprises: (a) a step of preparing a black fabric with no dust adsorbed thereon; (b) a step of photographing a surface of the fabric and acquiring a first surface image; (c) a step of attaching fine dust on the fabric and preparing a dust fabric; (d) a step of photographing a surface of the dust fabric with a camera and acquiring a second surface image; (e) a step of treating the dust fabric for clothing management and preparing a removal fabric; and (f) a step of photographing a surface of the removal fabric with the camera and acquiring a third surface image, and additionally comprises a step of dividing the brightness of pixels configuring the first, second, and third surface images into a plurality of phases, and acquiring a brightness value of all the pixels, and a step of comparing the brightness values of the second and third surface images or the first, second, and third surface images, and drawing a fine dust removal rate on the fabric surface. The present invention aims to provide the evaluation method of the removal rate of fine dust adsorbed on the fabric surface, which is able to objectively and quantitatively evaluate the performance for removing fine dust.

column12: VARIABLE VALVE LIFT DEVICE
column13: According to an embodiment of the present invention, a variable valve lift device includes: a cam shaft; a cam piece having one side with first cams having different lift amounts, having a first cam protruding portion formed adjacent to the first cams, rotated together with the cam shaft, and movably arranged on the cam shaft; a first guide pin formed to protrude from one side of the outer peripheral surface of the first cam protruding portion; a first guide arranged to correspond to the first cam protruding portion, and having first guide grooves such that the first cam piece is moved in one direction along the cam shaft according to rotation of the first guide pin; and a first driving part configured to move the first guide to a first cam protruding portion side such that the first guide pin is inserted into the first guide groove of the first guide. Therefore, the valve lift can be controlled in multi stages by forming the cams in the cam piece longitudinally moving on the cam shaft, and moving the cam piece in a longitudinal direction of the cam shaft by a structure of fastening the guide pin to the guide. A return protrusion formed on the cam piece pushes the guide to the outside to interrupt the longitudinal movement of the cam piece.

column13: The present invention relates to novel Lactobacillus plantarum S48 and P1201 strains having excellent conjugated linoleic acid productivity and acid and bile acid resistance. The present invention also relates to probiotics and food items rich in the conjugated linoleic acid. According to the present invention, the Lactobacillus plantarum S48 and P1201 strains have the excellent CLA productivity to be used to produce food items with increased CLA content. column12: HOT PRESS MOLD HAVING COOLING SYSTEM
column13: PURPOSE: A hot press mold having a cooling system is provided to secure stable and uniform transfer of cooling water in the mold by distributing cooling water from cooling water ducts through a cooling water distribution plate into cooling channels. CONSTITUTION: A hot press mold having a cooling system comprises a hose block, cooling water ducts(63), a cooling water distribution plate(64), and cooling channels(65). The hose block is made of a heat resistant material and coupled with a hose connected to a cooling water tank. The cooling water ducts connect cooling water supply paths to supply holes and connect cooling water discharge paths to discharge holes. The cooling water distribution plate has a plurality of openings that are connected to inlet and outlet paths. The cooling channels are distributed over the entire inside of a shaped steel and communicated with the openings formed in the cooling water distribution plate in order to circulate cooling water.

column12: SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE WITH A SEMICONDUCTOR DIE EMBEDDED BETWEEN AN EXTENDED SUBSTRATE AND A BOTTOM SUBSTRATE
column13: A method of manufacturing a semiconductor device having a semiconductor die within an extended substrate and a bottom substrate may include bonding a bottom surface of a semiconductor die to a top surface of a bottom substrate, forming an adhering member to a top surface of the semiconductor die, bonding an extended substrate to the semiconductor die and to the top surface of the bottom substrate utilizing the adhering member and a conductive bump on a bottom surface of the extended substrate and a conductive bump on the bottom substrate. The semiconductor die and the conductive bumps may be encapsulated utilizing a mold member. The adhering member may include a laminate film, a non-conductive film adhesive, or a thermal hardening liquid adhesive.

column12: CONTENT TRANSMISSION SYSTEM
column13: In order to easily prevent traffic of a content data server, which provides an arbitrary content, from being overloaded, the content transmission system according to an exemplary embodiment includes a content data server which provides an arbitrary content to a plurality of terminals when a request signal for the arbitrary content is input from the plurality of terminals, a data control server which when the arbitrary content is provided, monitors whether the traffic of the content data server is overloaded and if the traffic is overloaded as a result of monitoring, generates a traffic distribution request signal, and a node control server which when the traffic distribution request signal is input from the data control server, controls to provide the arbitrary content to an arbitrary distribution node, which satisfies a setting standard among a plurality of distribution nodes, to be provided to an arbitrary terminal among the plurality of terminals.

column12: METHOD FOR PROCESSING BYPRODUCTS OF PROCESSING SEA CUCUMBER
column13: PURPOSE: A processing method for sea cucumber byproducts is provided to have excellent industrial availability by utilizing water which is generated in a sea cucumber boiling process and discarded in a conventional method. CONSTITUTION: A processing method for sea cucumber water generated in a sea cucumber boiling process includes a step of obtaining butanol fractions by adding butanol in sea cucumber water generated in a sea cucumber boiling process. The sea cucumber water is the dry material of sea cucumber water. The processing method includes a step of obtaining butanol fractions by adding butanol in sea cucumber water after water is added in the dry material of sea cucumber. The processing method adds 10-30g of the dry material of sea cucumber water about 1L of water.

column12: Method for processing byproducts of processing sea cucumber
column13: The invention relates to a method for processing byproducts of processing sea cucumbers. The method uses waste boiled water for sea cucumbers which has good industrial utilizability properties. In addition, a composition obtained through the method which has natural antifungal activity-containing distillation substances has small side effects in comparison with one using chemical substances and a pro-environmental advantage. The composition which has natural antifungal activity-containing distillation substances are extracted from waste boiled water for sea cucumbers which can be easily obtained in market, and thus the method has economical and commercial utilization values. Moreover, the waste boiled water for sea cucumbers can be utilized but not wasted, and thus the method can play an active role in protection of nature.

column12: DEVELOPMENT OF MOLECULAR MARKERS TO SELECT HIGH OLEATE PEANUT(ARACHIS HYPOGAEA L.)
column13: PURPOSE: A molecular marker for determining Arachis hypogaea L. of high oleic acid is provided to accurately determine the species of the Arachis hypogaea L. CONSTITUTION: A molecular marker for determining Arachis hypogaea L. of high oleic acid contains a primer pair of sequence numbers 3 and 4 or a primer pair of sequence numbers 5 and 6. The Arachis hypogaea L. is F435. A method for determining Arachis hypogaea L. of high oleic acid comprises: a step of isolating DNA from a sample of Arachis hypogaea L.; a step of amplifying the DNA using the molecular marker as a primer; and a step of analyzing the amplified product by electrophoresis. A kit for determining Arachis hypogaea L. of high oleic acid contains the molecular marker.

column12: INTEGRATED RISK MANAGEMENT SYSTEM RELATED CUSTOMS ADMINISTRATION AND ITS METHOD
column13: The present invention relates to a system for integrally managing risk related to customs administration capable of providing a function related to an all selection module selecting risk information in a custom step and a work system in a custom administration office by applying the risk information monitored in an integrated risk management module to a complex risk model which is generated by combining the integrated risk management module, which performs the monitoring by collecting, classifying, and evaluating the risk information, with a plurality of risk elements. The present invention comprises a work cooperation module which feedbacks the risk information as information utilized for the integrated risk management module, the integrated selection module, etc. The method for integrally managing the risk related to the customs administration comprises a risk recognition step for comprising a process which collects and monitors the risk information; an information analysis step for comprising a process which analyzes the information collected in the risk recognition step; an analysis result applying step for generating a new risk type based on a relation between the risk components in the information analysis step; and a feedback and reevaluation step for giving feedback for the new risk type to the risk recognition step.
